window.docContents[11].resolve({"/Basic-Types/Maps-and-Sets/#zh-basictypes-maps-treeset-h008":{"contents":"非捆绑集将格式良好的证明与数据分开。\n这在定义 嵌套归纳类型 时主要有用。\n要使用这些变体，请导入模块 Std.TreeSet.Raw。\n\nTree sets without a bundled well-formedness invariant, suitable for use in nested\ninductive types. The well-formedness invariant is called Raw.WF. When in doubt, prefer TreeSet\nover TreeSet.Raw. Lemmas about the operations on Std.TreeSet.Raw are available in the\nmodule Std.Data.TreeSet.Raw.Lemmas.A tree set stores elements of a certain type in a certain order. It depends on a comparator function\nthat defines an ordering on the keys and provides efficient order-dependent queries, such as\nretrieval of the minimum or maximum.To ensure that the operations behave as expected, the comparator function cmp should satisfy\ncertain laws that ensure a consistent ordering:* If a is less than (or equal) to b, then b is greater than (or equal) to a\nand vice versa (see the OrientedCmp typeclass).* If a is less than or equal to b and b is, in turn, less than or equal to c, then a\nis less than or equal to c (see the TransCmp typeclass).Keys for which cmp a b = Ordering.eq are considered the same, i.e only one of them\ncan be contained in a single tree set at the same time.To avoid expensive copies, users should make sure that the tree set is used linearly.Internally, the tree sets are represented as size-bounded trees, a type of self-balancing binary\nsearch tree with efficient order statistic lookups.Internal implementation detail of the tree set.\n\nWell-formedness predicate for tree sets. Users of TreeSet will not need to interact with\nthis. Users of TreeSet.Raw will need to provide proofs of WF to lemmas and should use lemmas\nlike WF.empty and WF.insert (which are always named exactly like the operations they are about)\nto show that set operations preserve well-formedness. The constructors of this type are internal\nimplementation details and should not be accessed by users.Internal implementation detail of the tree map.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009地图和套装\u0009基于树的集合\u0009转换","header":"20.19.10.6.1. 非捆绑变体","id":"/Basic-Types/Maps-and-Sets/#zh-basictypes-maps-treeset-h008"},"/Namespaces-and-Sections/#namespaces-sections":{"contents":"名称被组织成分层的 namespaces，它们是名称的集合。\n命名空间是 Lean 中组织 API 的主要方式：它们提供操作本体，对相关项进行分组。\n此外，虽然这不是通过在命名空间中给它们命名来完成的，但 语法扩展、实例 和 属性 等功能的效果可以附加到命名空间。\n\n将操作排序到名称空间中可以从全局角度从概念上组织库。\n然而，任何给定的 Lean 文件通常不会同等地使用所有名称。\nSections 提供了一种对全局可用名称集合的本地视图进行排序的方法，以及精确控制编译器选项以及语言扩展、实例和属性的范围的方法。\n它们还允许使用 variable 命令集中声明并根据需要传播许多声明共享的参数。\n\n\n\n\n\n","context":"Lean 参考","header":"6. 命名空间和部分","id":"/Namespaces-and-Sections/#namespaces-sections"},"/Terms/Function-Types/#function-types":{"contents":"Lean 的函数类型不仅仅描述函数的域和共域。\n它们还提供了详细说明应用程序站点的说明，指示某些参数将通过统一或 类型类合成 自动发现，其他参数是可选的，具有默认值，而其他参数应使用自定义策略脚本进行合成。\n此外，它们的语法包含对缩写 curried 函数的支持。\n\nFunction types依赖函数类型包括显式名称：非依赖函数类型不会：\n\nCurried Function Types依赖函数类型可以包含在一组括号中具有相同类型的多个参数：这相当于为嵌套函数类型中的每个参数名称重复类型注释。\n\nImplicit, Optional, and Auto Parameters函数类型可以描述采用隐式参数、实例隐式参数、可选参数和自动参数的函数。\n除实例隐式参数外，所有参数都需要一个或多个名称。\n\nMultiple Parameters, Same TypeNat.add的类型可以这样写：* Nat → Nat → Nat* (a : Nat) → (b : Nat) → Nat* (a b : Nat) → Nat最后两种类型允许函数与 命名参数 一起使用；除此之外，这三个都是等效的。\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009条款","header":"13.2. 功能类型","id":"/Terms/Function-Types/#function-types"},"/The-Simplifier/Invoking-the-Simplifier/#simp-tactic-naming":{"contents":"Lean 的简化器可以通过多种方式调用。\n最常见的模式在一组策略中捕获。\n策略参考包含简化策略的完整列表。\n\n简化策略名称中均包含 simp。\n除此之外，它们是根据描述其功能的前缀和后缀系统命名的：\n\n -!后缀\n\n将 autoUnfold 配置选项设置为 true，使简化器展开所有定义\n\n -?后缀\n\n使简化器跟踪简化过程中使用的规则，并建议最小的 simp set 作为对策略脚本的编辑\n\n -_arith后缀\n\n允许使用线性算术简化规则\n\n d- 前缀\n\n导致简化器仅通过定义保留的重写来简化\n\n -_all后缀\n\n使简化器反复简化所有假设和目标结论，考虑尽可能多的假设，直到不可能进一步简化\n\n\n\n还有两个进一步的简化策略、simpa 和 simpa!，用于在实现目标之前同时简化目标和证明项或假设。\n这种同时简化使得证明对于 simp set 中的变化更加稳健。\n\n\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009简化者","header":"15.1. 调用简化器","id":"/The-Simplifier/Invoking-the-Simplifier/#simp-tactic-naming"},"/releases/v4.16.0/#markdown-17493634228065214670-h5":{"contents":"The Lean 4 library saw many changes that improve arithmetic reasoning, enhance data structure APIs,\nand refine library organization. Key changes include better support for bitwise operations, shifts,\nand conversions, expanded lemmas for Array, Vector, and List, and improved ordering definitions.\nSome modules have been reorganized for clarity, and internal refinements ensure greater consistency and correctness.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009发行说明\u0009Lean 4.16.0 (2025-02-03)\u0009Highlights","header":"Library updates","id":"/releases/v4.16.0/#markdown-17493634228065214670-h5"},"/releases/v4.22.0/#markdown-12134672518858847025-h1":{"contents":"\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009发行说明\u0009Lean 4.22.0 (2025-08-14)","header":"Highlights","id":"/releases/v4.22.0/#markdown-12134672518858847025-h1"},"/releases/v4.25.0/#markdown-14208528238065019496-h2":{"contents":"#10524 adds support for interactivity (hover, go-to-definitions) for \"try this\"\nmessages that were introduced in #9966. In doing so, it moves the link\nto apply a suggestion to a separate [apply] button in front of the\nsuggestion.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009发行说明\u0009Lean 4.25.0 (2025-11-14)\u0009Highlights","header":"Apply \"try this\" Suggestions","id":"/releases/v4.25.0/#markdown-14208528238065019496-h2"}});